data.name: PrintSettings
desc: These properties describe the printing of the content of a text document.

properties.name: PrintBlackFonts
desc: determines if characters are always printed in black.

properties.name: PrintControls
desc: determines if control shapes are printed.

properties.name: PrintEmptyPages
desc: determines if automatically inserted empty pages are printed.

properties.name: PrintFaxName
desc: contains the name of the fax.

properties.name: PrintGraphics
desc: determines if graphic objects are printed

properties.name: PrintLeftPages
desc: determines if left pages are printed.

properties.name: PrintPageBackground
desc: determines if the background color / background graphic of pages is printed.

properties.name: PrintPaperFromSetup
desc: specifies if the printer paper tray selection of the system printer is used.
If com.sun.star.view.PrintSettings.PaperFromSetup is FALSE, then the paper tray selection of the page styles is used.

properties.name: PrintProspect
desc: determines if prospect printing is used.

properties.name: PrintReversed
desc: determines if the pages are printed in the reverse order, starting with the last page.

properties.name: PrintRightPages
desc: determines if right pages are printed.

properties.name: PrintTables
desc: determines if text tables are printed.
